The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     IN THE CITY
                  
	 The Cricket Association of Bengal (CAB) after a working committee meeting on Wednesday has decided to postpone the felicitation of Sourav Ganguly. Sourav told us that he will be busy till December 9 So we have postponed it from December 7 to December 14  which is a Sunday, Jagmohan Dalmiya said at the Eden on Wednesday.      
	Meanwhile, the working committee has also decided to divide the districts into four zones. A plan for building one stadium for each zone has also been proposed.                
	FOOTBALL: Merchants Cup five-a-side meet at the Rangers Club from 6pm                                                                                                                                                                     
